                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="210680" author="ihara" created="Tue, 10 Oct 2017 00:18:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;ok, that workaround works. you can close this ticket.&lt;br/&gt;
However, after patch 22507 landed, default partition configuation for MDS caused huge performance regression. please check &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9998&quot; title=&quot;Default partition setup is not optimal for best metadata performance&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-9998&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-9998&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="209057" author="dmiter" created="Thu, 21 Sep 2017 14:07:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry for delay. This behavior is expected. Resently we changed the default value for CPU partitions.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/22507&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/22507&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So, now &lt;b&gt;cpu_pattern&lt;/b&gt; is specified and have default value &quot;&lt;b&gt;N&lt;/b&gt;&quot;. But&#160;if &lt;b&gt;cpu_pattern&lt;/b&gt; is specified, the &lt;b&gt;cpu_npartitions&lt;/b&gt; will be ignored.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You can return to previous behavior by spefifing empty value for&#160;&lt;b&gt;cpu_pattern&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So, please use the following configuration:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;options libcfs cpu_pattern=&quot;&quot;&#160;cpu_npartitions=10&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="206163" author="pjones" created="Wed, 23 Aug 2017 17:04:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Dmitry&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Can you please advise on this one?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Peter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
